title: Blaupunkt Travelpilot DX Benelux (2013-2014) navigation CD disk
description:
CD: Benelux 2013-2014 (there will be no further updates for the DX-series after this one)

Compatible with: Blaupunkt Travelpilot DX-series (tested with a DX-r52).

Also compatible with some OEM navigation radio's manufactured by Blaupunkt.

You'll need:
- An old IDE CD-burner (the slower, the better), ideally something from 2005 or older, without DVD capability.
- SlySoft Clone CD (trial), download here: http://www.slysoft.com/en/download.html
- A PC running Windows 7 (with IDE capabilities, or a good USB to IDE converter)
- Blank CD's

Instructions:
1. Blow the dust of your old CD-burner, TEST IT thoroughly before proceeding.
2. Copy the file "teleatlas.ccp" to "C:Program Files (x86)SlySoftCloneCDProfiles".
3. Launch SlySoft CloneCD, click 'I Agree', then click 'Try It!' for the trial version.
4. Select 'Write from imageFile' (CD icon with a pencil).
5. Click 'browse', select the file "cd2-BNL_2013_2014-MS_DXv1.ccd" from the "DX-BNL-2014" folder; click 'Open', then 'Next >'.
6. Put a blank CD in your CD-burner; now select your CD-burner and click 'Next >'.
7. IMPORTANT: set the 'Write Speed' to '4x (704 kByte/s)' (try a few different speeds if it doesn't work, but never exceed 8x).
8. IMPORTANT: select the 'teleatlas' profile; now click 'OK', then 'Try It!'.
9. Wait for it to complete; you can safely ignore the yellow warnings, that's just CloneCD telling you that sectors are being amplified.

Put the disk in your Blaupunkt Travelpilot DX-series radio and wait for it to load, try to enter an address in order to verify that it really works.

If it works: yay, now burn a second copy just to be safe!
If it does not work: 
 1) try a different burner,
 2) try different write speeds,
 3) use another brand of blank CD media.

(in this order, its usually the burner that's not capable enough).

I successfully burned this for a Travelpilot DX-r52
 using a Samsung Writemaster (Model SH-S182) CD-burner, connected via a generic IDE to USB adapter.
I'm running Windows 7 Pro x64, CloneCD version 5.3.1.4 (trial).

Source: gpsunderground.com topics and some fooling around.

(instructions are valid for all Travelpilot DX CD's from all countries)
